# Agent Memory

A `MEMORY.md` file at the repo root stores context that should persist across sessions.

## When to update

After completing a task, append to `MEMORY.md` if any of the following occurred:

- An architectural or technical decision was made
- A non-obvious bug was found and fixed
- The user expressed a preference not already captured in CLAUDE.md
- A workaround was needed due to a library limitation or quirk
- A big feature is added or removed

Do NOT record routine changes (file edits, dependency installs, standard CRUD).

## Format

Use the existing sections in `MEMORY.md`. Add entries as bullet points with a date prefix (`YYYY-MM-DD`). Keep entries to one or two sentences. If a section doesn't exist, create it.

## On session start

Read `MEMORY.md` at the beginning of a session when tackling a non-trivial task, to recall prior context.
